obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9100)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9100&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Sports Broadcasting`
  line `Signals (Mandatory Sharing with Prasar Bharati) Act, 2007.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided, it shall be deemed to have come into force on the 11th day of`
  line `November, 2005.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9101)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9101&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "broadcaster" means any person who provides a content broadcasting service and includes a`
  line `broadcasting network service provider when he manages and operates his own television or radio`
  line `channel service;`
  line
  line `(b) "broadcasting" means assembling and programming any form of communication content, like`
  line `signs, signals, writing, pictures, images and sounds, and either placing it in the electronic form on`
  line `electro-magnetic waves on specified frequencies and transmitting it through space or cables to make`
  line `it continuously available on the carrier waves, or continuously streaming it in digital data form on the`
  line `computer networks, so as to be accessible to single or multiple users through receiving devices either`
  line `directly or indirectly; and all its grammatical variations and cognate expressions;`
  line
  line `(c) "broadcasting service" means assembling, programming and placing communication content`
  line `in electronic form on the electro-magnetic waves on specified frequencies and transmitting it`
  line `continuously through broadcasting network or networks so as to enable all or any of the multiple`
  line `users to access it by connecting their receiver devices to their respective broadcasting networks and`
  line `includes the content broadcasting services and the broadcasting network services;`
  line
  line `(d) "broadcasting networks service" means a service, which provides a network of infrastructure`
  line `of cables or transmitting devices for carrying broadcasting content in electronic form on specified`
  line `frequencies by means of guided or unguided electro-magnetic waves to multiple users, and includes`
  line `the management and operation of any of the following:`
  line
  line `(i) Teleport/Hub/Earth Station,`
  line
  line `(ii) Direct-to-Home (DTH) Broadcasting Network,`
  line
  line `(iii) Multi-system Cable Television Network,`
  line
  line `(iv) Local Cable Television Network,`
  line
  line `(v) Satellite Radio Broadcasting Network,`
  line
  line `(vi) any other network service as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) "cable television channel" service means the assembly, programming and transmission by`
  line `cables of any broadcasting television content on a given set of frequencies to multiple subscribers;`
  line
  line `(f) "cable television network" means any system consisting of closed transmission paths and`
  line `associated signal generation, control and distribution equipment, designed to receive and re-transmit`
  line `television channels or programmes for reception by multiple subscribers;`
  line
  line `(g) "community radio service" means terrestrial radio broadcasting intended and restricted only to`
  line `a specific community and within specified territory;`
  line
  line `(h) "content" means any sound, text, data, picture (still or moving), other audio-visual`
  line `representation, signal or intelligence of any nature or any combination thereof which is capable of`
  line `being created, processed, stored, retrieved or communicated electronically;`
  line
  line `(i) "content broadcasting service" means the assembling, programming and placing content in`
  line `electronic form and transmitting or retransmitting the same on electromagnetic waves on specified`
  line `frequencies, on a broadcasting network so as to make it available for access by multiple users by`
  line `connecting their receiving devices to the network, and includes the management and operation of any`
  line `of the following:`
  line
  line `(i) terrestrial television service,`
  line
  line `(ii) terrestrial radio service,`
  line
  line `(iii) satellite television service,`
  line
  line `(iv) satellite radio service,`
  line
  line `(v) cable television channel service,`
  line
  line `(vi) community radio service,`
  line
  line `(vii) any other content broadcasting services as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(j) "Direct-to-Home (DTH) broadcasting service" means a service for multi-channel distribution`
  line `of programmes direct to a subscriber's premises without passing through an intermediary such as a`
  line `cable operator by up linking to a satellite system;`
  line
  line `(k) "Guidelines" means the Guidelines issued under section 5;`
  line
  line `(l) "multi-system cable television network" means a system for multi-channel downlinking and`
  line `distribution of television programmes by a land-based transmission system using wired cable or`
  line `wireless cable or a combination of both for simultaneous reception either by multiple subscribers`
  line `directly or through one or more local cable operators;`
  line
  line `(m) "Prasar Bharati" means the Corporation known as the Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting`
  line `Corporation of India) established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Prasar Bharati`
  line `(Broadcasting Corporation of India) Act, 1990 (25 of 1990);`
  line
  line `(n) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "satellite television service" means a television broadcasting service provided by using a`
  line `satellite, and received with or without the help of a local delivery system but does not include Directto-Home`
  line `delivery service;`
  line
  line `(p) "satellite radio service" means a radio broadcasting service provided by using a satellite and`
  line `directly receivable through receiver sets by multiple subscribers in India;`
  line
  line `(q) "service provider" means provider of a broadcasting service;`
  line
  line `(r) "specified" means specified under the Guidelines issued under section 5;`
  line
  line `(s) "sporting events of national importance" means such national or international sporting events,`
  line `held in India or abroad, as may be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette to be of`
  line `national importance;`
  line
  line `(t) "terrestrial television service" means a television broadcasting service provided over the air by`
  line `using a land-based transmitter and directly received through receiver sets by the public;`
  line
  line `(u) "terrestrial radio service" means a radio broadcasting service provided over the air by using a`
  line `land-based transmitter and directly received through receiver sets by the public.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act and defined in the Cable Television`
  line `Networks (Regulation) Act, 1995 (7 of 1995), the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24`
  line `of 1997), the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885), the Indian Wireless Telegraphy Act, 1933 (17 of`
  line `1933) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9102)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Mandatory sharing of certain sports broadcasting signals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9102&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No content rights owner or`
  line `holder and no television or radio broadcasting service provider shall carry a live television broadcast on`
  line `any cable or Direct-to-Home network or radio commentary broadcast in India of sporting events of`
  line `national importance, unless it simultaneously shares the live broadcasting signal, without its`
  line `advertisements, with the Prasar Bharati to enable them to re-transmit the same on its terrestrial networks`
  line `and Direct-to-Home networks in such manner and on such terms and conditions as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions under sub-section (1) shall also provide that the advertisement revenue`
  line `sharing between the content rights owner or holder and the Prasar Bharati shall be in the ratio of not less`
  line `than 75:25 in case of television coverage and 50:50 in case of radio coverage.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may specify a percentage of the revenue received by the Prasar Bharati`
  line `under sub-section (2), which shall be utilised by the Prasar Bharati for broadcasting other sporting events.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9103)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9103&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may specify penalties to be imposed, including suspension or`
  line `revocation of licence, permission or registration, for violation of various terms and conditions as may be`
  line `specified under section 3, subject to the condition that amount of a pecuniary penalty shall not exceed one`
  line `crore rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposed without giving a reasonable opportunity to the service`
  line `provider:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no act or omission on the part of any person after the 11th November, 2005 and`
  line `before the date of promulgation of the Sports Broadcasting Signals (Mandatory Sharing with Prasar`
  line `Bharati) Ordinance, 2007(Ord. 4 of 2007), shall be subjected to penalties.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9104)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of the Central Government to issue Guidelines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9104&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall take all`
  line `such measures, as it deems fit or expedient, by way of issuing Guidelines for mandatory sharing of`
  line `broadcasting signals with Prasar Bharati relating to sporting events of national importance:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Guidelines issued before the promulgation of the Sports Broadcasting Signals`
  line `(Mandatory Sharing with Prasar Bharati) Ordinance, 2007(Ord. 4 of 2007), shall be deemed to have been`
  line `issued validly under the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9105)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9105&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Guidelines issued by the Central Government for`
  line `Downlinking of Television Channels on the 11th November, 2005 and for Uplinking from India on the`
  line `2nd December, 2005 for mandatory sharing of the sports broadcasting signals shall be deemed to be valid`
  line `as if they have been issued under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgement, decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority, any action taken by the Central Government or the Prasar Bharati in pursuance of the`
  line `Guidelines referred to in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be and to have always been for all purposes in`
  line `accordance with the law, as if the Guidelines had been validly in force at all material times and`
  line `notwithstanding anything as aforesaid and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, no legal proceeding shall be maintained or continued in any court for the enforcement of any direction`
  line `given by any court or any decree or order which would not have been so given had the Guidelines been`
  line `validly in force at all material times.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9106)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of the Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9106&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9107)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Rules and Guidelines to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9107&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and Guidelines made and`
  line `issued, as the case may be, under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or Guidelines, or both Houses agree that the rule or Guidelines should not be made, the rule or`
  line `Guidelines shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or Guidelines.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9108)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9108&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The relevant provisions under the Guidelines for Downlinking of Television Channels`
  line `issued on the 11th November, 2005 and the Guidelines for Up linking from India issued on the 2nd`
  line `December, 2005 for mandatory sharing of sports broadcasting signals with Prasar Bharati, shall continue`
  line `to remain in force till fresh Guidelines are issued under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9109)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539&sectionId=9109&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00007_200711_1517807323539
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Sports Broadcasting Signals (Mandatory Sharing with Prasar`
  line `Bharati) Ordinance, 2007 (Ord. 4 of 2007) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Sports Broadcasting Signals (Mandatory Sharing with Prasar`
  line `Bharati) Ordinance, 2007 (Ord. 4 of 2007), anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
